content:
When an agent or supervisor joins an active voice call or messaging session and needs context quickly, catch them up with a real-time AI-generated summary of the conversation. This is known as Conversation Catch-Up.

Available in: Lightning Experience, Enterprise and Unlimited Editions with the Einstein for Service add-on.

To use Conversation Catch-Up:

1. Enable Einstein Generative AI in Setup.
2. From Setup, enter Work Summaries and select Einstein Work Summaries.
3. Turn on Einstein Work Summaries if it's not already on.
4. Click the Conversation Catch-Up tab.
5. Turn on Supervisor Summaries to show conversation summaries to supervisors when they start monitoring a voice call or messaging session.
6. Turn on Agent Summaries to show conversation summaries to agents when a voice call or messaging session is transferred to them from another agent or bot.

A conversation must have at least 10 text-based entries before a summary can be generated. Conversation Catch-Up is available in six languages: English, Spanish, French, German, Italian, and Japanese.
title: Conversation Catch-Up: Real-time Summaries for Service Cloud
